      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;convexity-and-concavity&#34;&gt;Convexity and Concavity&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-1&#34;&gt;Exercise 1&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Show that a function $ f $ is convex on an interval if and only if for all $ x, y $ in the interval and $ 0 &amp;lt; t &amp;lt; 1 $, we have:
&lt;/p&gt;
$$ f(tx + (1 - t)y) \leq tf(x) + (1 - t)f(y). $$&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-2&#34;&gt;Exercise 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let $ f $ and $ g $ be convex functions with $ f $ increasing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
